aa(lp251
VAt times, our search for understanding in Cape Town
p252
aVfelt like an impossible quest,
p253
aVand all I wanted to do was to give up
p254
aVand go home to my loving husband, Vidir,
p255
aVand our son.
p256
aVBut despite our difficulties,
p257
aVthis journey did result in a victorious feeling
p258
aVthat light had triumphed over darkness,
p259
aVthat something constructive could be built out of the ruins.
p260
aa(lp261
VI read somewhere
p262
aVthat you should try and be the person that you needed when you were younger.
p263
aVAnd back when I was a teenager,
p264
aVI would have needed to know that the shame wasn't mine,
p265
aVthat there's hope after rape,
p266
aVthat you can even find happiness,
p267
aVlike I share with my husband today.
p268
aVWhich is why I started writing feverishly upon my return from Cape Town,
p269
aVresulting in a book co-authored by Tom,
p270
aVthat we hope can be of use to people from both ends
p271
aVof the perpetrator-survivor scale.
p272
aVIf nothing else,
p273
aVit's a story that we would've needed to hear when we were younger.
p274
aa(lp275
VGiven the nature of our story,
p276
aVI know the words that inevitably accompany it \u2014
p277
aVvictim, rapist \u2014
p278
aVand labels are a way to organize concepts,
p279
aVbut they can also be dehumanizing in their connotations.
p280
aVOnce someone's been deemed a victim,
p281
aVit's that much easier to file them away as someone damaged,
p282
aVdishonored,
p283
aVless than.
p284
aVAnd likewise, once someone has been branded a rapist,
p285
aVit's that much easier to call him a monster \u2014
p286
aVinhuman.
p287
aVBut how will we understand what it is in human societies
p288
aVthat produces violence
p289
aVif we refuse to recognize the humanity of those who commit it?
p290
aVAnd how \u2014
p291
aa(lp292
V(Applause)
p293
aa(lp294
VAnd how can we empower survivors if we're making them feel less than?
p295
aVHow can we discuss solutions to one of the biggest threats
p296
aVto the lives of women and children around the world,
p297
aVif the very words we use are part of the problem?
