aa(lp345
VTE: What we did is not a formula that we're prescribing for others.
p346
aVNobody has the right to tell anyone else how to handle their deepest pain
p347
aVor their greatest error.
p348
aVBreaking your silence is never easy,
p349
aVand depending on where you are in the world,
p350
aVit can even be deadly to speak out about rape.
p351
aVI realize that even the most traumatic event of my life
p352
aVis still a testament to my privilege,
p353
aVbecause I can talk about it without getting ostracized,
p354
aVor even killed.
p355
aVBut with that privilege of having a voice
p356
aVcomes the responsibility of using it.
p357
aVThat's the least I owe my fellow survivors who can't.
p358
